newsitem.title: SINGAPORE: Singapore HSFO seen rangebound, supplies healthy.
newsitem.headline: Singapore HSFO seen rangebound, supplies healthy.

text.p: High sulphur fuel oil prices on Friday were expected to be rangebound as healthy supplies were expected to offset the gains in crude, brokers said.
Two local traders were expected to be active bidders. A trader told Reuters he expected fuel oil 180 centistoke levels to hover between Thursday's range of $121-$123 per tonne.
At least two majors were expected to continue to offer October barrels.
Two cargoes remained unsold in October from South Korea, a cargo from Japan and some supplies from the Mideast, traders said.
China are still seeking for cargoes, a trader in Hong Kong said. Bids are heard at $126-127 per tonne c+f south China.
October paper swaps were quoted lower at $119-$120 on crude losses, down from Thursday's $120.50-$122.75 in line with crude.
